      <h2>About [Company Name]</h2>
      <p>Add a bit about your company here.</p>

      <h2>Role Overview</h2>
      <p>As a UX Writer II at [Company Name], you will deepen your craft and contribute to the development of user-centric content across our digital experiences. With your growing expertise, you will handle broader feature-level content responsibilities and actively contribute to content strategy discussions. This role is ideal for someone with 2-5 years of experience who is ready to take on more complex content challenges and collaborate with cross-functional teams.</p>

      <h2>What You'll Do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Create and implement content strategies for product features and workflows</li>
        <li>Write clear, consistent UI copy that aligns with our brand voice</li>
        <li>Collaborate with designers and developers to ensure content meets user needs</li>
        <li>Conduct content audits and make recommendations for improvements</li>
        <li>Help maintain and evolve content style guides and documentation</li>
        <li>Participate in user research to inform content decisions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What We're Looking For</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Bachelor's degree in English, Communications, or related field, or equivalent practical experience</li>
        <li>2-5 years of experience in UX writing or content design</li>
        <li>Strong portfolio showcasing content strategy and UX writing work</li>
        <li>Excellent writing and editing skills with meticulous attention to detail</li>
        <li>Understanding of UX principles and content design best practices</li>
        <li>Experience with content management systems and collaboration tools</li>
        <li>Strong communication and presentation skills</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Join [Company Name]</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Be part of a rapidly growing company that's shaping the future of how people connect online</li>
        <li>Contribute to a product that impacts millions of users worldwide</li>
        <li>Enjoy a collaborative, inclusive, and creative work environment</li>
        <li>Benefit from competitive compensation and flexible work arrangements</li>
      </ul>

